            "creation_date": 1468653016,
            "body": "<p>In android, the code for drawing a circle using <code>Canvas<\/code> the <code>float<\/code> argument is in <code>pixels<\/code>. <\/p>\n\n<p><strong>you say <code>float<\/code>, is the <code>float<\/code> a pixel representation.<\/strong> <\/p>\n\n<p>Below is the sample code for converting dp to px and px to dp.<\/p>\n\n<blockquote>\n  <p>To convert dp to pixel.<\/p>\n<\/blockquote>\n\n<pre><code>public static int dp2px(Resources resource, int dp) {\n    return (int) TypedValue.applyDimension(TypedValue.COMPLEX_UNIT_DIP,   dp,resource.getDisplayMetrics());\n}\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<blockquote>\n  <p>To convert pixel to dp.<\/p>\n<\/blockquote>\n\n<pre><code> public static float px2dp(Resources resource, float px)  {\n    return (float) TypedValue.applyDimension(TypedValue.COMPLEX_UNIT_PX, px,resource.getDisplayMetrics());\n}\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p><a href=\"https://stackoverflow.com/questions/4605527/converting-pixels-to-dp\">Conversion Code is from here.<\/a><\/p>\n",
            "answer_id": 38408749,
            "question_id": 38321526,
            "last_edit_date": 1495535329
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "user_type": "does_not_exist",
                "display_name": "user4774371"
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 3.0",
            "score": 0,
            "is_accepted": false,
            "last_activity_date": 1468305402,
            "creation_date": 1468305402,
            "body": "<p>No. Float values will be in pixels. If you want (recommended) you can specify dp units in /res folder using dimen attribute<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>&lt;dimen name=\"radius\"&gt;12dp&lt;/dimen&gt;\n<\/code><\/pre>\n",
            "answer_id": 38321602,
            "question_id": 38321526
        }
